rComments: This professor is respectful and engaging. Class work is what is expected. Is accessible outside of class.
She really cares about her students.

Great prof! Gives lots of examples in class. She doesnt see all the powerpoints in class because she takes time to explain the PowerPoints we do see instead of just reading her slides. Always available for questions after class.

The exam questions are not reflective of the material at all. The formulation of the multiple choice is unclear and ambiguous. There are multiple correct answers in most questions. In lectures, she separates the material through several PowerPoint presentations which makes it heavy to review for exams, and she asks you to read most at home.
